### Memory Directory Enhancement

USP extends the standard Spec Kit `memory/` directory with an additional context file:

| File | Purpose | Injected Into |
|------|---------|---------------|
| `constitution.md` | Governing principles, non-negotiable rules | `/speckit.plan`, `/speckit.analyze` |
| `technical-architecture.md` | **[USP Addition]** Technology stack, application structure, integrations, testing strategy | `/speckit.specify`, `/speckit.plan`, `/speckit.tasks`, `/speckit.analyze` |

#### Why `technical-architecture.md`?

The constitution defines the *rules* (what you MUST/MUST NOT do), while the technical architecture provides *context* (what exists, how it's structured). Both are essential for AI agents to make informed decisions:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      memory/ Directory                          │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  constitution.md              technical-architecture.md         │
│  ┌─────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────────────┐       │
│  │ PRINCIPLES      │          │ CONTEXT                 │       │
│  │ • Rules         │          │ • Tech stack            │       │
│  │ • Constraints   │          │ • Project structure     │       │
│  │ • Gates         │          │ • Data architecture     │       │
│  │ • Governance    │          │ • Integrations          │       │
│  │                 │          │ • Testing strategy      │       │
│  │ "What you MUST  │          │ "What EXISTS and HOW    │       │
│  │  do/not do"     │          │  it's organized"        │       │
│  └─────────────────┘          └─────────────────────────┘       │
│                                                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Command Integration

The following commands MUST read `memory/technical-architecture.md`:

| Command | How It Uses Technical Architecture |
|---------|-----------------------------------|
| `/speckit.specify` | Understand existing tech to write compatible specs; identify integration points |
| `/speckit.plan` | Align plans with existing stack; reuse patterns; identify dependencies |
| `/speckit.tasks` | Generate tasks using correct file paths, frameworks, and conventions |
| `/speckit.analyze` | Validate consistency with existing architecture; flag deviations |

#### Template Location

Use the template at `templates/technical-architecture-template.md` when creating the initial `memory/technical-architecture.md` file.

