### Feature Finalization & Cleanup

USP introduces the `/speckit.finalize` command for completing features and cleaning up the workspace.

#### The `/speckit.finalize` Command

Use this command when a feature/story has been **tested and is ready to be completed**:

```text
/speckit.finalize
```

**What it does**:
1. **Updates status** - Marks the feature specification as "Completed"
2. **Integrates with Golden Specs** - Prompts user to create new or update existing
3. **Cleans up workspace** - Deletes the feature folder from `specs/inprogress/`

#### Finalization Workflow

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Feature Finalization                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  /speckit.finalize                                              │
│       │                                                         │
│       ▼                                                         │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐                │
│  │ Validate Completion                         │                │
│  │ • Check tasks.md for incomplete items       │                │
│  │ • Review checklists                         │                │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘                │
│       │                                                         │
│       ▼                                                         │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────-┐                │
│  │ Golden Spec Integration Choice               │               │
│  │                                              │               │
│  │ (A) Create NEW Golden Spec                   │               │
│  │     → New 001-xxx spec created               │               │
│  │                                              │               │
│  │ (B) Add to EXISTING Golden Spec              │               │
│  │     → Added as User Story to existing spec   │               │
│  │                                              │               │
│  │ (C) Skip Golden Spec integration             │               │
│  │     → Cleanup only                           │               │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────-┘               │
│       │                                                         │
│       ▼                                                         │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────-┐               │
│  │ Delete from specs/inprogress/                │               │
│  │ • Remove feature folder and all artifacts    │               │
│  │ • Clean workspace for next feature           │               │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────-┘               │
│                                                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Workspace Structure After Finalization

After finalization, the feature is preserved only in the Golden Spec (if integrated):

```
specs/
├── golden/                                # Golden Specs directory
│   ├── README.md                          # Index of all Golden Specs
│   ├── 001_user-authentication/           # Golden Spec (includes finalized features)
│   │   └── spec.md
│   ├── 002_project-management/
│   │   └── spec.md
│   └── ...
├── inprogress/                            # Active features directory
│   └── US54321_new-feature/                # Other active features remain
└── ...
```

#### Integration Options Explained

| Option | When to Use | What Happens |
|--------|-------------|--------------|
| **Create NEW Golden Spec** | Feature represents a new core capability | New `NNN_feature-name/` folder created with converted spec |
| **Add to EXISTING Golden Spec** | Feature extends/enhances existing capability | Added as new User Story to existing Golden Spec |
| **Skip** | One-time fix or temporary feature | Feature folder deleted without Golden Spec integration |

